parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose motive power, increasing the risk of a crash or fire.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the battery indicator light comes on
the dashboard lights flash
the windshield wipers turn on
and the alternator smokes or catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall or lose motive power, increasing the risk of a crash or fire.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the battery indicator light comes on
and the alternator smokes or catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump relay can cause the vehicle to stall or lose motive power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the fuel pump relay fails
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle control system can cause the vehicle to lose motive power or stall, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or stalls
the electronic throttle control warning light comes on
and the vehicle may experience abnormal acceleration or deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Totally Integrated Power Module (TIPM) can cause the vehicle to lose motive power or stall, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or stalls
the check engine warning light comes on
and the vehicle may experience electrical system failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences brake failure or reduced braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heated seat element can cause a fire, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The heated seat element catches fire
and smoke fills the cabin.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to lose motive power or stall, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The air suspension warning light comes on
and the vehicle loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brakes fail to respond
the vehicle takes longer to stop
and there may be a hissing sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the RAB system can cause the vehicle to fail to stop, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to stop
the brake pedal feels hard or spongy
and there may be a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates
the brakes fail to respond
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.
